          <h3>Overview</h3>
          <p>Party L/nes is an exercise in interactive storytelling. Through this art form, I wanted to explore design and data visualization as a way to enhance a user’s experience with a narrative.</p>

          <p>The project is based on the article <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/wonk/wp/2015/01/07/the-top-10-reasons-american-politics-are-worse-than-ever/" style="color: #ff2f18;">The Top 10 Reasons American Politics Are So Broken</a>, written by Jonathan Haidt and Sam Abrams. I also used a blurb from <a href="http://www.people-press.org/2014/06/12/political-polarization-in-the-american-public/#about-the-data" style="color: #ff2f18;">Pew Research Center</a>, along with Haidt and Abrams words, to enhance the introduction paragraph.</p>
