          <h3>Designing the Layout</h3>
          <p>The landing page of Party L/nes opens with a hero image. The hero image has a cinematic effect, which draws in a user’s attention. As the user scrolls down, the title fades to black, which further enhances this effect.</p> 

          <p>My initial thought for the layout of the article was to create dividers for the headers of each point in Haidt and Abrams list. Shown in my wireframes, these dividers would not only highlight the statements, but symbolically act as the lines between the two political parties. However, I quickly realized that these blocks disrupted the flow of the design and narrative. Therefore, I decided to increase the font size and underlined the points in order to set them apart from the rest of the content.</p>
