          <h3>Developing the Party L/nes Game</h3>
          <p>To leave a final impact on the user, I developed a game in JavaScript that asks he/she to agree or disagree with a series of quotes from 2016 Presidential candidates. These quotes are presented without the identity of the speaker. The final results displays how many quotes from Republicans and Democrats that the user agreed or disagreed with, along with the identity of the quote’s author. The hope is that the user questions his/her own beliefs without the influence of what a political party believes. This game was developed from a list of quotes gathered by <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2016/us/elections/candidates-on-the-issues.html?_r=0" style="color: #ff2f18;">The New York Times</a>.</p>
